## Data Formats

### Devices (`devices.txt`)

```
username|device_id|device_name|device_type|room|brand|model|status|power|brightness|temperature|mode|schedule_time
john_doe|1|Living Light|Light|Living|Philips|Hue|Online|on|75|||Auto|07:00
john_doe|2|Bedroom Thermostat|Thermostat|Bedroom|Nest|Learning|Online|on||72|Auto|22:00
jane_smith|3|Kitchen Camera|Camera|Kitchen|Ring|Indoor|Online|on||||Manual|
```

### Energy Logs (`energy_logs.txt`)

```
username|device_id|date|consumption_kwh
john_doe|1|2024-11-01|0.5
john_doe|2|2024-11-01|2.3
jane_smith|3|2024-11-01|0.2
```

### Automation Rules (`automation_rules.txt`)

```
username|rule_id|rule_name|trigger_type|trigger_value|action_device_id|action_type|action_value|enabled
john_doe|1|Morning Lights|Time|07:00|1|Turn|On|true
jane_smith|2|Night Thermostat|Time|22:00|2|Set|22|true
```

---

## Example: Device Control Page with Trigger-Value Filter

### 1. Navigation and Layout

- **Page ID:** `device-control-page`
- **Elements:**
  - Dropdown to select device by `device_id` or `device_name`
  - Display device details (`device-name-display`, `device-status-display`)
  - Controls (e.g., power toggle, brightness slider)
  - Energy consumption summary (`energy-summary`)
  - Automation rules table filtered by trigger value (`rules-table`)
  - Buttons: `apply-filter-button`, `save-settings-button`, `back-to-dashboard`

### 2. Filter Automation Rules by Trigger Value

- User selects a trigger type (e.g., Time, Power status, Motion detected)
- User inputs or selects a trigger value (e.g., "07:00", "On", "Motion")
- On clicking `apply-filter-button`, the system filters `automation_rules.txt` for rules matching the selected trigger type and value.
- Display filtered rules in `rules-table` with columns: Rule Name, Trigger Type, Trigger Value, Action Device, Action Type, Action Value, Enabled.

### 3. Device Control Actions

- Power toggle button (`power-toggle-{device_id}`) to turn device On/Off.
- Brightness slider for lights.
- Temperature setting for thermostats.
- Schedule time input.

### 4. Energy Consumption Display

- Show total and daily consumption from `energy_logs.txt` for the selected device.
- Display in `energy-summary` container.

